reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Blazing Fast Performance and Reliable Storage: Fikwot FN500 1TB NVMe SSD Delivers Perfect B550
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded my system with the Fikwot FN500 1TB NVMe SSD, and the difference in performance is nothing short of remarkable. This M.2 2280 solid-state drive has become the powerhouse of my setup, providing speed and reliability that have exceeded my expectations.The 3D NAND technology, coupled with the PCIe Gen3 x4 interface, ensures lightning-fast data transfer rates. Whether I'm loading large applications, editing high-resolution videos, or transferring hefty files, the FN500 handles it all with ease. The speed boost is immediately noticeable, and it has significantly reduced loading times across the board.Installation was a breeze, thanks to the M.2 form factor, and the drive's compatibility with PCIe Gen3 x4 ensures that I'm getting the most out of my system's capabilities. The drive's slim profile also helps in maintaining a clean and organized internal setup.One of the standout features of the FN500 is its reliability. The drive is built with durability in mind, and the 1.3 version PCIe ensures a stable and consistent performance over time. I appreciate the peace of mind that comes with knowing my data is secure and easily accessible whenever I need it.The 1TB storage capacity is perfect for my needs, providing ample space for my growing collection of files, games, and multimedia projects. The NVMe architecture not only enhances speed but also optimizes power efficiency, contributing to a more energy-efficient system.In conclusion, the Fikwot FN500 1TB NVMe SSD has exceeded my expectations in terms of speed, reliability, and ease of installation. Whether you're a gamer, content creator, or just someone looking to breathe new life into their system, this SSD is an excellent investment. It's a game-changer that delivers on its promises, and I highly recommend it to anyone in search of top-notch storage performance.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best-priced SSD ever! FAST! Clone worked first try
reviews.reviewText: I got this product to replace the old 1TB SSD in my ASUS Rog Zephyrus G14. I'm a software programmer and was consistently running out of space on my laptop. However, I didn't exactly want to pay a lot of money for a Samsung SSD, and this SSD was on sale for $160 for 4TB. I thought it could be a bit fishy, but considering the feedback that was already received, I thought this SSD was worth the investment. I went for the 7350MB/s model because paying extra for +50MB/s seemed pointless, and my laptop would probably not see a big difference between the two models. Upon receiving the SSD, I thought cloning would be hard. I used a simple M.2 enclosure from best buy to facilitate the transfer, along with some online software I found.Installing was as simple as discharging my hands, opening up the laptop, and plugging the new SSD in. Upon rebooting my laptop, the bit-level clone on this new SSD worked first-try, so I didn't need to reinstall Windows or any other programs. Unity now builds my projects about 3x faster and programs that took a couple seconds to open up now open instantly. The SSD is even at 2% usage maximum when playing a game. I loaded up World of Warcraft and saw a drastic increase in my FPS, and cranked up the textures in Fortnite to "Epic" and still saw an increase in performance from when I previously ran the game on "Medium" textures.In conclusion, this SSD is a lot better than other M.2s on the market and didn't require extra drivers. To clone my data, I opened up the disk partitioner and initialized the disk in partition-table format, then created a single new volume on it. From there, I was able to identify the disk in the downloaded cloning software, which made more partitions on the drive and then cloned it. Cloning 1TB (minus 156gb) of data took about 30 minutes, then I shut down the computer and replaced the drive. Upon installation, the PC immediately booted up normally and I didn't have to install any software. A driver prompt appeared at first which I accepted, and after 1 restart, the only thing different with my PC was the new storage space and some crazy speed from this new SSD.I definitely recommend this, solid 10+1 out of 10.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Upgraded my PS5
reviews.reviewText: Ordered this for my PS5 to expand the storage as it was a very good price for 2TB. The heat sink doesn't come attached but that was a non-issue as it was very easy to do. Installed in the PS5 per Sony's instructions. Powered it back up and the drive was recognized immediately, prompting to be formatted for use. That was it. This drive is also faster then the internal drive (particularly on writes it seems), so moving games onto it can give you a slight performance boost.

Aber heutzutage darf ja jeder dau sein unwissen verkünden🤭.
